# CVEs suppressed for the weekly Trivy scan (security-scan.yml).
#
# The Tailscale binary is a statically-linked Go program; Trivy attributes
# Go-stdlib CVEs to it that are already patched in the tailscale/go toolchain
# but that Trivy can't see the fixed version for. Add specific CVE IDs here with
# a one-line justification when they prove to be unfixable noise. Keep this list
# tight — a genuinely fixed CVE against tailscaled is the signal to bump
# TS_VERSION in the Dockerfile, not to ignore it.
